l they finally managed to fix the problem (for new wizards starting the epic, the ones who'd already done the prequest were SOL), I sincerely doubt he did anything to lower his own faction.  That being said, no GM will help you on this matter.  You only have a couple of options:<br>
<br>
1) Reset your faction in Sol Ro, then do faction work to raise Truespirit.  You don't have to redo the 2k though, look up the shaman epic and do the early step over and over again to raise the faction.  (Something about spawning &quot;a lesser spirit&quot; in OOT or RM then handing in an item in FP.)  Or you can go the fast way and redo the wizard epic steps, which is what I did when Kandin wouldn't talk to me.  You lose 2k, but it only takes an hour and you're ready to finish your epic.<br>
<br>
2) Get another wizard with good epic faction to get you a gear (they aren't nodrop), get your oil with that, then do the invis trick to hand in the items.  I don't know if this even works anymore, and I wouldn't recommend it.  I doubt a GM would be very willing to help you recover your lost epic items if he discovered you used invis to try and raise your faction artificially. <br>
<br>
The bug is stupid and gave a lot of people grief, but it's there and you'll have to work around it, if you want your epic.  It's not hard to do luckily, just takes a bit more work.  <br>
